JOHANNESBURG, April 25 Following are major news items in leading South
African newspaper Saturday: The Citizen: -- A controversial new draft
legislation aimed at significantly restructuring the liquor industry is in
the process of being finalized and will be presented to the cabinet within
the next three weeks, the Department of Trade and Industry said
Friday. Saturday Star: -- Managing the transformation of the South African
National Defense Force (SANDF) forms part of the huge task that awaits
Lieutenant General Siphiwe Nyanda, the man widely expected to succeed SANDF
chief General Georg Meiring when he steps down next month.
